713759f-a.title: Manhattan: 55th Street (East) - Lexington Avenue
713759f-a.text:
55th Street, north side, west from 145 East 55th, east of Lexington Avenue. The church is the Swedish Baptist Church, and beyond it
is the Babies Hospital.
March 28, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.

713760f-a.title: Manhattan: 55th Street (East) - Lexington Avenue
713760f-a.text:
135, 137 and 139-141 East 55th Street (left to right), at, adjoining and east of the N.E. corner of Lexington Ave., showing the International Medical Centre (formerly the Babies Hospital); a four story residence and the American Music Hall (formerly the Swedish Baptist Church).
September 18, 1937.
George D. Chinn.
